text: Often times I see indie games with great presentation hiding a mediocre core underneath. It's not the case with Anodyne as it plays well and the level design is quite memorable. It's no surprise it was one of my favorite games in 2013. This 2-part theme represents the game's atmosphere very well with its dreamy vibes.
